# Open Questions Check

## The Rule

Before implementing code that depends on an unresolved design decision, check [MANIFEST.md §18](../../MANIFEST.md#18-open-questions--pending-decisions) to ensure the relevant question is resolved.

All Phase 1 and Phase 2 blocking decisions are **resolved**. The remaining open items are Phase 3 scope:

## Remaining Open Questions (Phase 3 Blockers)

| # | Question | Impacts |
|---|----------|---------|
| 1 | Image/video optimization strategy | `image`, `imageGrid`, `video` lazy loading |
| 2 | State persistence across sessions (localStorage opt-in) | `defineConfig({ persistence })` |
| 3 | `parameterPanel` schema format | `parameterPanel` component |
| 4 | Multi-page support model (`ui.page()`) | `ui.page()`, `ui.navigate()` |

## All Phase 1 + 2 Decisions — Locked

These are **resolved** and must not be re-opened without updating MANIFEST.md:

| Decision | Resolution |
|----------|-----------|
| Execution model | `app()` once per connection; button callbacks; handles |
| Wire format | `FRAGMENT` messages (HTML); `outerHTML` swap on client |
| State | Nanostores server-side only; `ConnectionScope` per connection |
| Layout | `shell()` + `grid()` — no standalone `sidebar()`, no `columns()` |
| CSS | Self-contained `lastriko.css`; no Pico.css; no CDN |
| Client rendering | `outerHTML` swap; no diffing library; no framework |
| Plugin isolation | `plugin → core` only |
| streamText | Handle-based; `.append(chunk)` + `STREAM_CHUNK`; no re-run |
| table | `TableHandle` with `.prepend/.append/.remove/.onRowClick`; `RowHandle.update()` |
| metric | `MetricHandle`; value is always `string`; `.update(value, opts?)` |
| text | `TextHandle`; `.update(content)` pushes `FRAGMENT` |
| Hot reload | Phase 1–2: full reset. Phase 3+: `hotReloadPreserve: true` (default) preserves inputs, scroll, active tabs |
| Button lock | `btn.setLoading(true/false)` |

## How to Resolve a Question

1. Make a decision
2. Add a row to MANIFEST.md §18 changing status from ⏳ to ✅
3. Update the relevant component spec doc
4. Update MANIFEST.md changelog
5. Commit manifesto update separately from the code change
